members.name: TIFF_BYTE
members.comment: Flag for 8 bit unsigned integers.

members.name: TIFF_ASCII
members.comment: Flag for null-terminated ASCII strings.

members.name: TIFF_SHORT
members.comment: Flag for 16 bit unsigned integers.

members.name: TIFF_LONG
members.comment: Flag for 32 bit unsigned integers.

members.name: TIFF_RATIONAL
members.comment: Flag for pairs of 32 bit unsigned integers.

members.name: TIFF_SBYTE
members.comment: Flag for 8 bit signed integers.

members.name: TIFF_UNDEFINED
members.comment: Flag for 8 bit uninterpreted bytes.

members.name: TIFF_SSHORT
members.comment: Flag for 16 bit signed integers.

members.name: TIFF_SLONG
members.comment: Flag for 32 bit signed integers.

members.name: TIFF_SRATIONAL
members.comment: Flag for pairs of 32 bit signed integers.

members.name: TIFF_FLOAT
members.comment: Flag for 32 bit IEEE floats.

members.name: TIFF_DOUBLE
members.comment: Flag for 64 bit IEEE doubles.

members.name: TIFF_IFD_POINTER
members.comment: Flag for IFD pointer defined in TIFF Tech Note 1 in TIFF Specification Supplement 1.

members.name: MIN_DATATYPE
members.comment: The numerically smallest constant representing a TIFF data type.

members.name: MAX_DATATYPE
members.comment: The numerically largest constant representing a TIFF data type.

members.name: UNKNOWN_TAG_NAME
members.comment: The name assigned to a tag with an unknown tag number. Such a tag may be created for example when reading an IFD and a tag number is encountered which is not in any of the TIFFTagSets known to the reader.

members.name: getSizeOfType
members.comment: Returns the number of bytes used to store a value of the given data type.

param: dataType - the data type to be queried.
throws: IllegalArgumentException - if datatype is less than MIN_DATATYPE or greater than MAX_DATATYPE.
return: the number of bytes used to store the given data type.

members.name: getName
members.comment: Returns the name of the tag, as it will appear in image metadata.

members.name: getNumber
members.comment: Returns the integer used to represent the tag.

members.name: getDataTypes
members.comment: Returns a bit mask indicating the set of data types that may be used to store the data associated with the tag. For example, a tag that can store both SHORT and LONG values would return a value of:  (1 << TIFFTag.TIFF_SHORT) | (1 << TIFFTag.TIFF_LONG)

return: an int containing a bitmask encoding the set of valid data types.

members.name: getCount
members.comment: Returns the value count of this tag. If this value is positive, it represents the required number of values for a TIFFField which has this tag. If the value is negative, the count is undefined. In the latter case the count may be derived, e.g., the number of values of the BitsPerSample field is SamplesPerPixel, or it may be variable as in the case of most US-ASCII fields.

return: the value count of this tag.

members.name: isDataTypeOK
members.comment: Returns true if the given data type may be used for the data associated with this tag.

param: dataType - the data type to be queried, one of TIFF_BYTE, TIFF_SHORT, etc.
throws: IllegalArgumentException - if datatype is less than MIN_DATATYPE or greater than MAX_DATATYPE.
return: a boolean indicating whether the given data type may be used with this tag.

members.name: getTagSet
members.comment: Returns the TIFFTagSet of which this tag is a part.

members.name: isIFDPointer
members.comment: Returns true if this tag is used to point to an IFD structure containing additional tags. A TIFFTag represents an IFD pointer if and only if its TIFFTagSet is non-null or the data type TIFF_IFD_POINTER is legal. This condition will be satisfied if and only if either getTagSet() != null or isDataTypeOK(TIFF_IFD_POINTER) == true. Many TIFF extensions use the IFD mechanism in order to limit the number of new tags that may appear in the root IFD.

return: true if this tag points to an IFD.

members.name: hasValueNames
members.comment: Returns true if there are mnemonic names associated with the set of legal values for the data associated with this tag. Mnemonic names apply only to tags which have integral data type.

return: true if mnemonic value names are available.

members.name: addValueName
members.comment: Adds a mnemonic name for a particular value that this tag's data may take on. Mnemonic names apply only to tags which have integral data type.

param: name - the name to associate with the value.

members.name: getValueName
members.comment: Returns the mnemonic name associated with a particular value that this tag's data may take on, or null if no name is present. Mnemonic names apply only to tags which have integral data type.

return: the mnemonic name associated with the value, as a String.

members.name: getNamedValues
members.comment: Returns an array of values for which mnemonic names are defined. The method getValueName() will return non-null only for values contained in the returned array. Mnemonic names apply only to tags which have integral data type.

return: the values for which there is a mnemonic name.

members.comment: Constructs a TIFFTag with a given name, tag number, set of legal data types, and value count. A negative value count signifies that either an arbitrary number of values is legal or the required count is determined by the values of other fields in the IFD. A non-negative count specifies the number of values which an associated field must contain. The tag will have no associated TIFFTagSet. If there are mnemonic names to be associated with the legal data values for the tag, addValueName() should be called on the new instance for each name. Mnemonic names apply only to tags which have integral data type. See the documentation for getDataTypes() for an explanation of how the set of data types is to be converted into a bit mask.

param: number - the number used to represent the tag.
dataTypes - a bit mask indicating the set of legal data types for this tag.
count - the value count for this tag.
throws: NullPointerException - if name is null.
IllegalArgumentException - if number is negative or dataTypes is negative or specifies an out of range type.

members.comment: Constructs a TIFFTag with a given name, tag number and TIFFTagSet to which it refers. The legal data types are set to include TIFF_LONG and TIFF_IFD_POINTER and the value count is unity. The TIFFTagSet will represent the set of TIFFTags which appear in the IFD pointed to. A TIFFTag represents an IFD pointer if and only if tagSet is non-null or the data type TIFF_IFD_POINTER is legal.

param: number - the number used to represent the tag.
tagSet - the TIFFTagSet to which this tag belongs.
throws: NullPointerException - if name or tagSet is null.
IllegalArgumentException - if number is negative.

members.comment: Constructs a TIFFTag with a given name, tag number, and set of legal data types. The value count of the tag will be undefined and it will have no associated TIFFTagSet.

param: number - the number used to represent the tag.
dataTypes - a bit mask indicating the set of legal data types for this tag.
throws: NullPointerException - if name is null.
IllegalArgumentException - if number is negative or dataTypes is negative or specifies an out of range type.

name: javax.imageio.plugins.tiff.TIFFTag
comment:
A class defining the notion of a TIFF tag. A TIFF tag is a key that may appear in an Image File Directory (IFD). In the IFD each tag has some data associated with it, which may consist of zero or more values of a given data type. The combination of a tag and a value is known as an IFD Entry or TIFF Field.

The actual tag values used in the root IFD of a standard ("baseline") tiff stream are defined in the BaselineTIFFTagSet class.

see: BaselineTIFFTagSet, TIFFField, TIFFTagSet
